The rebel Rwandan Patriotic Front (RPF) has  captured Rwanda's most important market town, a meeting place for traders from  neighbouring countries, RPF radio Muhabura claimed in a broadcast monitored on  Friday by the BBC.
The radio said the rebels took Ruhango Trading Centre, 54 kilometres (32  miles) south of the Rwandan capital Kigali, on Friday.
The market is a meeting point for traders from neighbouring Burundi,  Zaire, Tanzania and Uganda, the radio added.
